02/11/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Police are working to identify the perpetrators of a bomb attack that targeted police in Athens on Friday (29 October), according to a police statement Monday. 
Authorities say they are close to identifying the DNA of one of the attackers. 
No group has claimed responsibility for the attack, but police suspect it was the work of a leftist radical group. 
The bomb damaged police buses, but caused no casualties. 
(MPA - 01/11/04)
